 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.509","title":"[audit][fix] GradedScope::close() must preserve leak panic on error","description":"Fresh-eyes diff audit of src/obligation/graded.rs. Verify the live GradedScope::close() error-path change against Drop leak-panic semantics; patch and validate if it suppresses the intended invariant enforcement.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Codex","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:06:30.464853162Z","created_by":"Codex","updated_at":"2026-04-01T18:16:06.592642147Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T18:12:14.928668511Z","close_reason":"Current tree already preserves GradedScope leak panic on close error; focused rch regression close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations passed.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","diff","graded","obligation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.509","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:06:30.464853162Z","created_by":"Codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2873,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.509","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: Fresh-eyes audit shows the bead appears stale against the current tree. src/obligation/graded.rs already only marks GradedScope.closed on successful close() and preserves the Drop leak panic on Err (see close() + close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations). Agent Mail inbox/register/list calls are still failing with transient mailbox DB errors, so this bead comment is the durable coordination trail while I run the focused rch-backed regression.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:09:47Z"},{"id":2874,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.509","author":"Codex","text":"Completed 2026-04-01. This bead was stale on current HEAD: commit cb375e77 already fixed the GradedScope::close() regression by only setting self.closed on success and added close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations to pin the Drop leak-panic invariant. Re-validated via rch only: cargo test -p asupersync --lib close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations -- --nocapture (pass on vmi1293453, confirms SCOPE LEAKED panic still fires on Err) and cargo check -p asupersync --lib (pass, exit=0 on vmi1156319). Agent Mail register/list/fetch remains unavailable due transient database errors, so this Beads comment is the durable coordination record.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:13:34Z"},{"id":2875,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.509","author":"Codex","text":"Completed 2026-04-01. Fresh-eyes diff audit of src/obligation/graded.rs found that the live change to GradedScope::close() set self.closed=true on the error path, which suppresses the intended Drop leak panic and violates the file’s own close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations contract. Restored the original invariant by leaving self.closed=false when close() returns Err. Validation via rch exec with isolated cargo dirs passed: cargo fmt --check, cargo check -p asupersync --lib, cargo test -p asupersync --lib close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations -- --nocapture, and cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings. Agent Mail is still unavailable: register/list/fetch continue to fail with transient database errors.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:15:21Z"},{"id":2876,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.509","author":"ubuntu","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: Focused stale-audit verification complete. Live tree already preserves the intended invariant: GradedScope::close() only sets closed=true on success, leaves closed=false on Err, and Drop still panics on leaked obligations. Validation via rch: cargo test -p asupersync --lib obligation::graded::tests::close_err_drop_panics_on_outstanding_obligations -- --exact --nocapture => PASS on worker vmi1227854.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:16:06Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.51","title":"[audit][web] Make SessionLayer duplicate cookie parsing match CookieJar last-value semantics","description":"src/web/session.rs::get_cookie currently returns the first matching cookie pair, while src/web/extract.rs::CookieJar overwrites duplicates and therefore resolves the last value. That lets the same request produce different cookie values depending on whether SessionLayer or CookieJar reads it, and stale/attacker-controlled duplicates can shadow the value the rest of the web stack would observe. Align SessionLayer with CookieJar by making duplicate cookies resolve to the last value, add focused helper and middleware regressions, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverMaple","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:53:05.075753069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:18.124857027Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:18.124857027Z","close_reason":"Duplicate of asupersync-1qfd0.50; fix and validation already landed/closed there","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:18.124820278Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cookies","session","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.51","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:53:05.075753069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","title":"[audit][diff] Verify grpc streaming buffer cap saturates and recovers","description":"Fresh-eyes diff audit of src/grpc/streaming.rs. Verify the new MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED/resource_exhausted backpressure behavior for StreamingRequest and ResponseStream, patch if needed, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Codex","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:16:36.547954842Z","created_by":"Codex","updated_at":"2026-04-01T18:48:32.489617549Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T18:23:10.910571370Z","close_reason":"Fresh-eyes diff audit passed: grpc streaming buffer cap saturates with ResourceExhausted, recovers after a drain, and targeted rch validation is green.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","diff","grpc","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:16:36.547954842Z","created_by":"Codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2877,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: Fresh-eyes diff audit complete on src/grpc/streaming.rs. Verified the new MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED/resource_exhausted backpressure guard is applied symmetrically in StreamingRequest::push_result and ResponseStream::push, and that one drained slot re-enables a subsequent push. Validation via rch: cargo test --lib push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain => PASS (2 tests: streaming_request_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain, response_stream_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain); rch exec -- cargo fmt --check -- src/grpc/streaming.rs => PASS.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:23:10Z"},{"id":2879,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: picked up this diff-audit slice after repo/README archaeology. Current HEAD already has MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED caps plus focused saturation/recovery tests in src/grpc/streaming.rs. Running rch-backed targeted validation now: streaming_request_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain and response_stream_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain. Agent Mail bootstrap on this host is still degraded by local mailbox DB/server corruption, so beads are the reliable coordination trail until MCP registration is restored.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:24:38Z"},{"id":2880,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 start: auditing the live src/grpc/streaming.rs buffer-cap diff. Agent Mail is currently unreachable at the transport layer (http://127.0.0.1:8765/mcp/), so Beads comments are the coordination trail. Initial review focus: whether MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED/resource_exhausted preserves backpressure semantics, allows recovery after drain, and does not break terminal close/error behavior. I am inspecting call sites and will validate with rch-backed targeted cargo tests before closing or patching.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:25:06Z"},{"id":2881,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"ubuntu","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: Claimed fresh diff-audit slice for src/grpc/streaming.rs. Live diff adds MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED resource-exhausted caps on StreamingRequest/ResponseStream, but had no direct regression coverage for saturation plus recovery-after-drain. Agent Mail is currently unavailable from this session (local MCP transport to 127.0.0.1:8765 is refusing requests), so this bead comment is the durable coordination trail while I validate the new cap behavior via rch-backed targeted tests/clippy.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:26:09Z"},{"id":2882,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 progress update: fresh-eyes audit found that the live diff in src/grpc/streaming.rs only capped the module-local ResponseStream, but the crate’s public grpc::ResponseStream is re-exported from src/grpc/client.rs (see src/grpc/mod.rs) and remained unbounded. I patched the real exported surface too by making MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED pub(crate), applying the same resource_exhausted guard in src/grpc/client.rs::ResponseStream::push, and adding a focused regression test there for saturation and recovery after draining one slot. I am validating both the messaging fix and this gRPC audit through rch-backed targeted cargo commands before closing the beads.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:30:45Z"},{"id":2884,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 targeted validation update: all gRPC saturation behavior checks now pass remotely via rch. response_stream_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain passes for both grpc::streaming::tests and the newly added grpc::client::tests public-surface regression, and streaming_request_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain also passes. A broader clean-cache cargo check is running in parallel before I close the bead.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:39:01Z"},{"id":2885,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"ubuntu","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: Added direct regression coverage in src/grpc/streaming.rs for the live MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED diff. New tests pin both saturation-at-cap and recovery-after-drain for StreamingRequest and ResponseStream. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/grpc/streaming.rs => PASS locally; rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-codex-grpc-streaming-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib => PASS; rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-codex-grpc-streaming-clippy-tests cargo clippy -p asupersync --tests -- -D warnings => PASS; rch exec -- env CARGO_HOME=/tmp/rch-cargo-home-codex-grpc-response CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-codex-grpc-streaming-response-exact2 cargo test -j1 -p asupersync --lib grpc::streaming::tests::response_stream_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain -- --exact --nocapture => PASS. One request-side exact rerun hit a test-filter mismatch (0 matched) rather than a code failure; the worker-side cc crate corruption on vmi1156319 was isolated by forcing a clean CARGO_HOME on the passing response lane.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:41:54Z"},{"id":2888,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.510","author":"Codex","text":"Completed 2026-04-01. Fresh-eyes diff audit found that the live src/grpc/streaming.rs change only hardened the module-local ResponseStream, while the crate’s public grpc::ResponseStream is re-exported from src/grpc/client.rs and remained unbounded. Fix: share MAX_STREAM_BUFFERED at pub(crate) visibility, apply the same resource_exhausted guard in src/grpc/client.rs::ResponseStream::push, and add a public-surface regression test there. Validation via rch: response_stream_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain now passes for both grpc::streaming::tests and grpc::client::tests, streaming_request_push_rejects_when_buffer_full_and_recovers_after_drain passes, cargo fmt --check (pass), clean-cache cargo check -j1 -p asupersync --features messaging-fabric --all-targets (pass), and clean-cache cargo clippy -j1 -p asupersync --features messaging-fabric --lib -- -D warnings (pass). Repo-wide caveat: clean-cache cargo clippy --all-targets is currently blocked by unrelated pre-existing violations in tests/fabric_replay_scenarios.rs.","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:48:32Z"}]}
