 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","title":"[audit][websocket] Remove ambient entropy from client frame masking","description":"src/net/websocket/frame.rs currently generates client masking keys with direct getrandom::fill(), and src/audit/ambient.rs treats that as a critical unresolved ambient-authority violation. Replace the frame-mask path with EntropySource plumbing, use Cx entropy where WebSocket client/server/split APIs already have a context, add targeted regressions, and update the ambient-audit catalog/tests so the critical finding is actually retired.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverQuarry","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747405470Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747405470Z","close_reason":"Completed: websocket masking entropy now flows through EntropySource/Cx; rch cargo check --all-targets and focused websocket/audit lib tests passed; repo-wide clippy frontier is unrelated in http_client/debounce","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747380313Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","security","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","title":"[audit][websocket] Repair encode_with_entropy borrow call sites after entropy plumbing","description":"The in-progress ambient-entropy websocket changes updated FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy to take &Frame, but several call sites in src/net/websocket/frame.rs, src/net/websocket/client.rs, and src/net/websocket/split.rs still pass Frame by value. That leaves the repo uncompilable and blocks rch-backed validation for unrelated work. Apply the minimal borrow-site fixes only, preserve the existing entropy-plumbing changes, add no new behavior beyond restoring compilation, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CoralCompass","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966871456Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966871456Z","close_reason":"Current tree already satisfies bead contract; websocket encode_with_entropy call sites already borrow frames","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966849596Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2476,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","author":"CoralCompass","text":"Audit result: current tree already satisfies this bead.

Source evidence:
- `src/net/websocket/frame.rs:393` still defines `FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy(&self, frame: &Frame, ...)`.
- `src/net/websocket/frame.rs:774` already borrows in the encoder implementation (`self.encode_with_entropy(&frame, ...)`).
- Client-side websocket call paths already borrow frames at `src/net/websocket/client.rs:438`, `:463`, `:485`, `:591`, and `:597`; the helper that reaches the codec also takes `frame: &Frame` at `src/net/websocket/client.rs:603`.
- Split-side websocket call paths already borrow frames at `src/net/websocket/split.rs:292`, `:437`, `:548`, and `:577`; the helpers that reach the codec take `frame: &Frame` at `src/net/websocket/split.rs:444` and `:584`.
- File-local formatting check passed: `rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/net/websocket/frame.rs src/net/websocket/client.rs src/net/websocket/split.rs`.

Conclusion: the borrow-site repair described by this bead is already present in the current tree; no code change required.","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:45:41Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.53","title":"[audit][service] Make LoadBalancer::call_balanced honor Service::poll_ready","description":"LoadBalancer::call_balanced() clones a backend and invokes service.call(req) directly without first driving Service::poll_ready on that clone. That violates the Service contract and can break middleware-backed services that reserve tokens/permits/state in poll_ready (e.g. rate/concurrency limiters or any custom service that arms itself there). Patch src/service/load_balance.rs so balanced dispatch only calls backends that have been polled ready on the exact clone being used, add focused regressions for a backend that panics if call happens before poll_ready, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CobaltRidge","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:55:18.665997964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.761662812Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.761662812Z","close_reason":"Implemented LoadBalancer::call_balanced poll_ready fix with regressions; crate lib check/clippy pass via rch, lib tests currently blocked by pre-existing src/web/session.rs E0382","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.761631023Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","load-balance","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.53","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:55:18.665997964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}

@@ -1597,42 +1597,42 @@ mod tests {
         let mut stream = ResponseStream::<u32>::open();
         let mut first_reader = stream.clone();
         let mut second_reader = stream.clone();
-        let first_wakes = Arc::new(AtomicUsize::new(0));
-        let second_wakes = Arc::new(AtomicUsize::new(0));
-        let first_waker = counting_waker(&first_wakes);
-        let second_waker = counting_waker(&second_wakes);
+        let first_wake_count = Arc::new(AtomicUsize::new(0));
+        let second_wake_count = Arc::new(AtomicUsize::new(0));
+        let first_reader_waker = counting_waker(&first_wake_count);
+        let second_reader_waker = counting_waker(&second_wake_count);

-        assert!(poll_stream(&mut first_reader, &first_waker).is_pending());
-        assert!(poll_stream(&mut second_reader, &second_waker).is_pending());
+        assert!(poll_stream(&mut first_reader, &first_reader_waker).is_pending());
+        assert!(poll_stream(&mut second_reader, &second_reader_waker).is_pending());

         stream
             .push(Ok(7))
             .expect("push should wake pending readers");
         assert_eq!(
-            first_wakes.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
+            first_wake_count.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
             1,
             "first cloned reader lost its wakeup",
         );
         assert_eq!(
-            second_wakes.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
+            second_wake_count.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
             1,
             "second cloned reader should also be notified",
         );

         assert!(matches!(
-            poll_stream(&mut first_reader, &first_waker),
+            poll_stream(&mut first_reader, &first_reader_waker),
             Poll::Ready(Some(Ok(7)))
         ));
-        assert!(poll_stream(&mut second_reader, &second_waker).is_pending());
+        assert!(poll_stream(&mut second_reader, &second_reader_waker).is_pending());

         stream.close();
         assert_eq!(
-            second_wakes.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
+            second_wake_count.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
             2,
             "close should wake the still-pending cloned reader",
         );
         assert!(matches!(
-            poll_stream(&mut second_reader, &second_waker),
+            poll_stream(&mut second_reader, &second_reader_waker),
             Poll::Ready(None)
         ));
     }
